\subsection{Method \code{open_short()}}{
Open a Short Position (Borrow and Sell)

Borrows the base asset and sells it immediately. This is how you bet
that an asset's price will go \strong{down}. The exchange automatically
borrows the asset you are selling (you don't need to call \code{borrow()}
separately).

\strong{What happens under the hood:}
\enumerate{
\item KuCoin borrows the base asset (e.g. BTC) on your behalf.
\item That borrowed asset is immediately sold on the market.
\item You now owe the borrowed amount plus interest.
\item Use \code{close_short()} later to buy it back and repay.
}
\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api.kucoin.com/api/v3/hf/margin/order}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/margin-trading/orders/add-order}{KuCoin Margin Add Order}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

